<p><em>922.43 Mbps</em> download and <em>932.64 Mbps</em> upload. Thatâ€™s awfully quick<sup id="fnref:fn-speed" role="doc-noteref"><a href="#fn:fn-speed" class="footnote" rel="footnote">1</a></sup>. To put the download speed into perspective, itâ€™s roughly 37x faster than what my parents pay for outside of Atlanta, and about 12x faster than what my roommate and I pay for in the city.</p>

<p>Maybe one day soon I can get gigabit internet in my apartment since Atlanta has been targeted by Google to <a href="https://fiber.google.com/cities/atlanta/" title="Google Fiber Atlanta.">bring Google Fiber to parts of the city</a>, with AT&amp;T and Comcast <a href="http://arstechnica.com/business/2015/06/comcast-2gbps-fiber-to-launch-in-a-bunch-of-markets-this-month/" title="Comcast Gigabit Internet.">soon to follow</a>.</p>

